Mussidae (clade XXI) is an exclusively Atlantic clade, and in contrast to Lobophylliidae , has costate coenosteum, regular (pointed) midcalice tooth tip, transverse septal crosses (as clusters or carinae), and no extensive stereome thickening (
Budd et al. , 2012
).

