Colonial; submassive or massive. Budding exclusively intracalicular. Corallites monomorphic; uniserial . Monticules may be present. Walls fused. Calice width usually medium (
4 – 15 mm
), with medium relief (
3 – 6 mm
). Costosepta mostly confluent. Septa in ≥ 4 cycles (≥ 48 septa). Free septa irregular. Septa spaced six to 11 septa per 5 mm . Costosepta unequal in relative thickness. Columellae trabecular and spongy (> 3 threads), <1/4 of calice width, and discontinuous amongst adjacent corallites with lamellar linkage. Internal lobes usually absent. Epitheca well developed. Endotheca low – moderate (tabular) ( Fig. 6A, D ).

